{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "◁ Definition 3.2 (Possibility Morphisms).",
    "Given possibility framesF = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩ and F ′ = ⟨S ′, ⊑ ′, {R ′ i } i∈I, P ′ ⟩, a possibility morphism from F to F ′ is a function h: S → S ′such that for all x ∈ S and i ∈ I:1.",
    "⊑-matching -∀X ′ ∈ P ′: ↓ ′ h(x) ∩ X ′ = ∅ iff ↓x ∩ h -1 [X ′] = ∅; 2.",
    "R-matching -∀X ′ ∈ P ′: R ′ i (h(x)) ⊆ X ′ iff R i (x) ⊆ h -1 [X ′]; 3. pull back -∀X ′ ∈ P ′: h -1 [X ′] ∈ P. 20A strict possibility morphism from F to F ′ is a function h: S → S ′ satisfying pull back such that for all x, y ∈ S, y ′, z ′ ∈ S ′, and i ∈ I:4.",
    "⊑-forth -if y ⊑ x, then h(y) ⊑ ′ h(x); 5."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}